{
  "stem": "8784.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In fact, I was assigned to work in a stone quarry, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which actually improved my life, because in the stone quarry, while it was extremely hard work, there was a little better supply of food for those that worked in the stone quarry.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I remember one incident where I was in the barracks of the concentration camp, and it was a huge barrack-- I don't know how many people would been there, but it could've been 1,000 people, people sleeping on three-high berth.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I was on the top one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And people would usually sleep in a manner that they would be with their heads towards the center of the room rather than towards the wall because they always wanted to hear and see what was going on.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "If they had to react to something, they would, they, they would be able to do that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I remember being in one of those-- sleeping on that high berth one day when an SS man came into the barrack and yelled out, Urbach!",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Now, as I described before, the fear was constant.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "It was always there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "The, the, the, necessity to respond and listen to the German orders was always there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So when the SS guard inside the barrack yelled out Urbach, another fellow stuck out his head, responded to the, to the call of Urbach.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I, not being sure whether he was calling me or my name or some other similar name, I also stuck out my head.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So now the SS guard was confused on who he really is supposed to be picking up.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So he took the two of us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And he took us down to the SS guards' [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] quarters.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
